The Thandiwe hitmaker took to Instagram to show off the rewards of hard work. He bought himself with a Range Rover worth R1.1 million."Just trying to inspire u cause I'm inspired every single day of my life," the singer wrote in the caption. His comment section was flooded with congratulatory messages including some from his industry friends such as actor Akhumzi Jezile and singer Amanda Black.A post shared by Vusi Nova (@vusinova1) on Mar 14, 2017 at 4:37am PDT 